window.bookSummaryJSON = "It was supposed to be a few relaxing days in the mountains for Nash Jaramillo and his Viet Nam Army buddies, target shooting and drinking beer. Then they discovered that the New Mexico valley where Nash had his cabin had been taken over by international terrorists with an explosive agenda. Cut off from the outside world, the old soldiers had no choice but to take on an enemy force that outnumbered them five to one. Over fifty years ago in Viet Nam these four men had fought for their country and survived, and now they were determined to do it again. You must read this exciting and action-packed follow-up to <i>Broken Heroes</i>, in which age and experience are pitted against evil intentions with deadly results. <br>"; 
